## 8. TYPOGRAPHY SYSTEM

Typography is a design medium. Use it as one.

### 8.1 Type Scale (Desktop)
```
Display:    72px–96px  / weight 700–900 / tight letter-spacing (-0.02em to -0.04em)
H1:         48px–64px  / weight 700–800 / letter-spacing -0.02em
H2:         36px–48px  / weight 700     / letter-spacing -0.01em
H3:         24px–30px  / weight 600     / letter-spacing 0
H4:         20px–24px  / weight 600     / letter-spacing 0
Body large: 18px–20px  / weight 400     / line-height 1.7
Body:       16px–18px  / weight 400     / line-height 1.65
Caption:    13px–14px  / weight 400–500 / letter-spacing 0.02em
Label:      11px–13px  / weight 600     / letter-spacing 0.08em / UPPERCASE
```

### 8.2 Type Scale (Mobile)
```
H1:         36px–48px
H2:         28px–36px
H3:         20px–24px
Body:       16px
Caption:    13px
```

### 8.3 Font Pairing Rules
Never use a single font for everything. Use 2 typefaces maximum per project.

| Brand Type         | Display Font             | Body Font                  |
|--------------------|--------------------------|----------------------------|
| Premium SaaS       | Cal Sans, Geist, Sora    | DM Sans, Plus Jakarta Sans |
| Luxury Brand       | Cormorant, Playfair      | Jost, Outfit               |
| Creative Agency    | Neue Haas Grotesk, Clash | DM Mono, Syne Mono         |
| Local Service      | Lexend, Nunito           | Inter, Source Sans         |
| Editorial/Blog     | Lora, Libre Baskerville  | Source Serif, Literata     |
| E-commerce         | Bricolage Grotesque       | DM Sans, Manrope           |
| Tech/Developer     | Space Grotesk, IBM Plex  | JetBrains Mono (code)      |

**Rules:**
- Load only the font weights you use: typically 400, 600, 700, 800
- Subset fonts when using Google Fonts or Fontsource
- Display fonts must be used ONLY for headings — never for body text
- Body fonts must maintain high readability at all sizes

### 8.4 Typography as Design
- Use oversized characters as decorative elements (large "01", "&", or quotes)
- Mix type weights within a headline (normal word + **Bold word**)
- Use gradient or color fill on select heading words
- Use a horizontal rule (line) between a label and a heading for premium feel
- Stack words vertically in wide hero headlines for editorial effect

### 8.5 Mistakes to Avoid
- Using the same font size for H2, H3, and body — there must be clear contrast
- Centered body text (never center more than 3 lines of paragraph text)
- Justified text on the web (causes uneven word spacing)
- Light weight (300) for small text — unreadable
- Line heights under 1.4 for body text
- Too many font families (max 2)

