## 9. COLOR SYSTEM

Never choose colors randomly. Build a complete, intentional system for every project.

### 9.1 Color System Structure
```
--color-primary:      Main brand color. Used for CTAs, active states, headings
--color-primary-dark: Darker shade for hover states on primary elements
--color-secondary:    Supporting color. Used for accents, icons, tags
--color-accent:       High-energy pop color. Used sparingly for emphasis
--color-neutral-50:   Lightest background
--color-neutral-100:  Section background, card backgrounds
--color-neutral-200:  Borders, dividers
--color-neutral-500:  Muted text, placeholders
--color-neutral-800:  Body text
--color-neutral-950:  Headings, dark backgrounds
--color-surface:      Card and panel background
--color-text-primary: Default text color
--color-text-muted:   Secondary text
--color-border:       Borders and dividers
--color-error:        Form validation error
--color-success:      Form success, confirmation states
```

### 9.2 Color Psychology Guide

| Industry / Emotion     | Color Direction                             |
|------------------------|---------------------------------------------|
| Trust / B2B SaaS       | Deep blue (#0047AB), neutral whites         |
| Energy / Consumer App  | Electric blue, coral, or orange accents     |
| Luxury / Premium       | Midnight navy, warm ivory, muted gold       |
| Health / Wellness      | Sage green, warm beige, cream               |
| Finance / Legal        | Dark navy, forest green, charcoal           |
| Creative / Agency      | High contrast black/white + bold accent pop |
| Food / Restaurant      | Warm terracotta, cream, forest green        |
| Technology / Dev       | Deep indigo, electric cyan, dark neutral    |
| Eco / Sustainability   | Earthy green, sand, warm neutrals           |

### 9.3 Gradient Usage
- Use gradients for: hero backgrounds, CTA sections, card highlights, text fills
- Max 2 gradient directions per page
- Gradient colors must come from the defined palette — not arbitrary values
- Avoid rainbow gradients. Two-color or subtle mesh gradients read premium.
- Use mesh gradients (CSS or SVG) for modern SaaS aesthetics

### 9.4 Dark Mode
- Build with CSS variables from the start — dark mode is a variable swap
- Do not use pure black (#000000) — use near-black (#0A0A0F or similar)
- Surfaces in dark mode: use layered dark grays, not flat black
- Ensure all text meets WCAG AA contrast in both modes
- Provide `prefers-color-scheme: dark` media query support

### 9.5 Contrast Requirements
- Body text on background: minimum 4.5:1 ratio (WCAG AA)
- Large text (18px+ bold): minimum 3:1 ratio
- UI components and focus indicators: minimum 3:1 ratio
- Test all color combinations with a contrast checker before shipping

### 9.6 Mistakes to Avoid
- Using 4+ distinct colors with no relationship to each other
- Using pure black and pure white only (this looks like a prototype)
- Choosing colors because they "look nice" without brand or psychology grounding
- Dark text on dark background
- Light text on light background
- Using accent color everywhere (it loses meaning)

