## 10. SPACING AND LAYOUT SYSTEM

### 10.1 Container Widths
```css
--container-sm:  640px   /* Narrow content: blog, article, legal */
--container-md:  768px   /* Forms, modals, focused content */
--container-lg:  1024px  /* Standard content sections */
--container-xl:  1280px  /* Wide sections, default page container */
--container-2xl: 1440px  /* Full-width hero sections */
```

Always use `max-width` + `margin: 0 auto` + horizontal padding for containers.

### 10.2 Section Padding Scale
```css
--section-padding-sm: 64px  0;    /* Compact sections: logos, dividers */
--section-padding-md: 96px  0;    /* Standard sections */
--section-padding-lg: 128px 0;    /* Hero, final CTA, featured sections */
--section-padding-xl: 160px 0;    /* Full-screen hero sections */
```

Mobile: divide desktop padding by 2 (64px → 32px, 128px → 64px).

### 10.3 Spacing Scale (8px base)
```
4px   — micro gaps (icon to label)
8px   — tight spacing (badge padding, small gaps)
12px  — compact inner spacing
16px  — standard component padding
24px  — card inner padding
32px  — gap between related elements
48px  — gap between sections within a group
64px  — gap between major sections
96px  — section padding (mobile)
128px — section padding (desktop)
```

### 10.4 Grid System
```css
/* Standard 12-column grid */
.grid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(12, 1fr);
  gap: 24px;
}
/* Breakpoints */
/* Desktop:  12 columns */
/* Tablet:   8 columns  */
/* Mobile:   4 columns  */
```

Common grid patterns:
- 4+4+4 (3 equal columns): features, benefits
- 8+4 (wide + narrow): feature + screenshot
- 6+6 (halves): problem/solution
- 3+3+3+3 (4 equal): pricing, team members
- Full-width: hero, CTA, section breaks

### 10.5 White Space Usage
- White space is not empty space — it is breathing room that creates premium perception
- Increase spacing between sections as content importance decreases
- Group related elements with tight spacing; separate distinct elements with generous spacing
- Never let text touch edges — minimum 16px horizontal padding on mobile

### 10.6 Responsive Breakpoints
```css
--bp-sm:  640px   /* Mobile landscape */
--bp-md:  768px   /* Tablet */
--bp-lg:  1024px  /* Desktop */
--bp-xl:  1280px  /* Wide desktop */
--bp-2xl: 1536px  /* Ultra-wide */
```

