## 12. MOTION AND ANIMATION RULES

### 12.1 Principles
- Every animation must have a purpose (guide attention, provide feedback, or reveal content)
- Animations must not delay content or block interaction
- Always respect `prefers-reduced-motion` media query
- Default: fast and subtle. Premium, not flashy.

### 12.2 Entrance Animations
Use staggered fade-up or fade-in for content sections:
```css
@keyframes fadeUp {
  from { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(20px); }
  to   { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); }
}
/* Trigger on intersection with IntersectionObserver or Framer Motion viewport */
```
- Duration: 0.4s–0.6s
- Easing: `cubic-bezier(0.16, 1, 0.3, 1)` (spring-like)
- Stagger delay: 0.08s–0.12s between children

### 12.3 Hover Interactions
- Buttons: background color shift + subtle shadow increase
- Cards: translateY(-4px) + shadow intensify
- Links: underline slides in from left
- Images: subtle scale(1.03) with overflow hidden on container
- Magnetic buttons (for key CTAs): translate toward cursor using JS mousemove

### 12.4 Scroll Animations
- Use `IntersectionObserver` for scroll-triggered reveals
- Or Framer Motion's `whileInView` prop
- Trigger when 15%–20% of element is visible
- Do not animate every element — only section openers and key content blocks

### 12.5 Parallax
- Use only for hero backgrounds and featured image sections
- Parallax shift: 20px–50px max. Not 200px.
- Use CSS `transform: translateY()` driven by scroll event — not `background-attachment: fixed` (causes jank)
- Never use parallax on mobile

### 12.6 Page Transitions
- Use opacity fade or slide-up transition between routes
- Duration: 0.25s–0.4s
- Do not use complex 3D transitions on content-heavy pages

### 12.7 Reduced Motion
```css
@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
  *, *::before, *::after {
    animation-duration: 0.01ms !important;
    transition-duration: 0.01ms !important;
  }
}
```
Always implement. No exceptions.

### 12.8 Mistakes to Avoid
- Animations that take over 0.8s — they feel sluggish
- Bouncing or elastic animations on every element
- Auto-playing carousels that move without user input
- Scroll-hijacking (overriding native scroll behavior)
- Animations that block content from being readable

