## 19. CURSOR IMPLEMENTATION INSTRUCTIONS

### 19.1 Project Stack
Default to this stack unless the project specifies otherwise (this repo is a **Vite + React + TypeScript** SPA, not Next.js):
- **Build tool & dev server:** Vite 5+ (`vite`, `vite build`, `vite preview`)
- **UI library:** React 18+ with TypeScript — client-rendered components only; **do not** use React Server Components, server-only APIs, or Next.js data-fetching patterns
- **Routing:** `react-router-dom` — use `<Routes>`, `<Route>`, nested routes, and `<Link>` / `<NavLink>` for internal navigation (**never** `next/link` or file-based Next routing)
- **Document head & SEO tags:** `react-helmet-async` (`Helmet`, `HelmetProvider`) for per-route `<title>`, meta description, canonical, Open Graph, and Twitter cards — **never** Next.js `metadata` exports, `<Head>` from `next/head`, or `app/layout` head conventions
- **Styling (this project):** Tailwind CSS v3 (utility-first; production CSS is purged via PostCSS). If a different repo has no Tailwind, use **CSS Modules** (e.g. `Component.module.css`) or plain CSS files co-located with components, imported from TS/TSX, and keep the same design tokens as CSS variables in a global stylesheet
- **Animation:** Prefer CSS transitions, `@keyframes`, and `IntersectionObserver` for scroll-driven reveals (no extra dependency). Optionally use **Framer Motion** only when it is already listed in that project’s `package.json`
- **UI Components:** shadcn/ui-style Radix primitives + Tailwind (as in this template) or fully custom components — same composition patterns, no Next-specific wrappers
- **Icons:** Lucide React or Phosphor Icons
- **Fonts:** Self-hosted `@font-face` in CSS, Fontsource packages imported in the entry or global CSS, or Google Fonts linked from `index.html` — use `font-display: swap` — **never** `next/font` or `next/font/local`
- **Images:** Standard `<img>` with `width`, `height`, `alt`, `loading`, and `srcset`/`sizes` as needed — **never** `next/image` or the Next.js image optimization loader
- **Entry:** `index.html` → `src/main.tsx` (calls `createRoot`) → `App.tsx` (providers, router). Do not assume `pages/_app`, `layout.tsx`, or `src/app/` exist

**Hard bans for this stack (do not generate):** `next/*` imports, App Router or Pages Router file conventions, `metadata` / `generateMetadata`, default `export const runtime`, Server Actions, `next/image`, `next/link`, `next/navigation`, `next/router` (Pages), or any pattern that requires a Node server rendering React per request unless the user explicitly asks for a different framework.

### 19.2 Design Token Setup
Always define design tokens as CSS custom properties in the **global** stylesheet (this project typically uses `src/index.css`; other repos may use `src/styles/globals.css` — follow the repo). The examples below apply regardless of filename:
```css
:root {
  --color-primary: #2563EB;
  --color-primary-dark: #1D4ED8;
  --color-secondary: #7C3AED;
  --color-accent: #F59E0B;
  --color-neutral-50: #F8FAFC;
  --color-neutral-100: #F1F5F9;
  --color-neutral-200: #E2E8F0;
  --color-neutral-500: #64748B;
  --color-neutral-800: #1E293B;
  --color-neutral-950: #020617;
  --color-surface: #FFFFFF;
  --color-text-primary: #1E293B;
  --color-text-muted: #64748B;
  --color-border: #E2E8F0;
  --radius-sm: 6px;
  --radius-md: 10px;
  --radius-lg: 16px;
  --radius-xl: 24px;
}
```
Map these to Tailwind in `tailwind.config.ts`:
```ts
theme: {
  extend: {
    colors: {
      primary: 'var(--color-primary)',
      secondary: 'var(--color-secondary)',
      accent: 'var(--color-accent)',
      surface: 'var(--color-surface)',
      border: 'var(--color-border)',
    }
  }
}
```

### 19.3 Component-Based Architecture
Organize by feature and layout responsibility. A Vite + React Router SPA often matches:
```
index.html              # Root HTML shell, favicon, default lang
src/
  main.tsx              # createRoot, StrictMode, import global CSS (`index.css`)
  App.tsx               # HelmetProvider, data/UI providers, BrowserRouter, Routes, shared layout chrome
  index.css             # Tailwind directives + CSS variables / base styles (or split tokens into styles/tokens.css)
  pages/                # Route-level views (e.g. Index.tsx, Contact.tsx) — thin: compose sections, wire data
  components/
    ui/                 # Base design system: Button, Card, Input, Badge (shadcn-style primitives)
    layout/             # Header, Footer, Container, Section, shell wrappers
    sections/           # Hero, Features, Testimonials, Pricing, FAQ, CTA
    blocks/             # Reusable sub-components within sections
  lib/
    utils.ts            # cn() helper, constants, shared helpers
  hooks/                # Shared hooks (media query, reduced motion, etc.)
```
Add `src/assets/` for static images processed by Vite; reference them with `new URL('./file.webp', import.meta.url).href` or `import img from './file.webp'` depending on convention. Use `public/` only for files that must keep exact URLs (e.g. `robots.txt`, verified domain files).

### 19.4 Reusable Section Wrapper
```tsx
// components/layout/Section.tsx
interface SectionProps {
  children: React.ReactNode;
  className?: string;
  id?: string;
  variant?: 'default' | 'muted' | 'dark' | 'accent';
}

export function Section({ children, className, id, variant = 'default' }: SectionProps) {
  const variants = {
    default: 'bg-white',
    muted: 'bg-neutral-50',
    dark: 'bg-neutral-950 text-white',
    accent: 'bg-primary text-white',
  };
  return (
    <section id={id} className={cn('py-24 lg:py-32', variants[variant], className)}>
      <div className="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        {children}
      </div>
    </section>
  );
}
```

### 19.5 Motion Patterns (CSS-first; Framer Motion optional)
In Vite SPAs, prefer **CSS transitions / `@keyframes`** plus **`IntersectionObserver`** (or a tiny hook) for section reveals so bundles stay lean. The patterns below with **`motion.*`** apply **only** when the project already depends on `framer-motion`; do not add the dependency solely for trivial fades unless the user asks.

```tsx
// Staggered children reveal (Framer Motion — use only if installed)
const container = {
  hidden: { opacity: 0 },
  show: {
    opacity: 1,
    transition: { staggerChildren: 0.1 }
  }
};

const item = {
  hidden: { opacity: 0, y: 20 },
  show: { opacity: 1, y: 0, transition: { duration: 0.5, ease: [0.16, 1, 0.3, 1] } }
};

// Usage
<motion.ul variants={container} initial="hidden" whileInView="show" viewport={{ once: true, margin: "-100px" }}>
  {items.map(i => <motion.li key={i.id} variants={item}>{i.content}</motion.li>)}
</motion.ul>
```

### 19.6 Clean Tailwind Patterns (and CSS Modules fallback)
When Tailwind is available, compose utilities and `cn()` as the default. When Tailwind is **not** installed, mirror the same structure using **CSS Modules**: import `styles from './Button.module.css'`, use `className={styles.primary}`, and keep token alignment with `:global(:root)` variables.

```tsx
// ✅ Good: component class extracted
function Button({ variant, children }: ButtonProps) {
  return (
    <button className={cn(
      "inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-lg px-6 py-3 text-sm font-semibold transition-all duration-150",
      variant === 'primary' && "bg-primary text-white hover:bg-primary-dark shadow-sm hover:shadow-md",
      variant === 'ghost' && "border border-border text-neutral-800 hover:bg-neutral-50"
    )}>
      {children}
    </button>
  );
}

// ❌ Bad: inline styles, repeated class strings, no abstraction
<div style={{ backgroundColor: '#2563EB', padding: '12px 24px', borderRadius: '8px' }}>...</div>
```

### 19.7 Schema JSON-LD Implementation
Inject JSON-LD from **route-level page components** together with other head tags. With **`react-helmet-async`**, colocate schema with the page that owns the entity (adjust provider wiring to match the repo — this project wraps the tree in `HelmetProvider` in `App.tsx` around `BrowserRouter`).

```tsx
// Example: src/pages/Contact.tsx (or any page component)
import { Helmet } from 'react-helmet-async';

export default function ContactPage() {
  const schema = {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "LocalBusiness",
    "name": "Company Name",
    "url": "https://company.com",
    "telephone": "+1-555-000-0000",
    "address": {
      "@type": "PostalAddress",
      "streetAddress": "123 Main St",
      "addressLocality": "City",
      "addressRegion": "State",
      "postalCode": "12345"
    }
  };

  return (
    <>
      <Helmet>
        <title>Contact | Company Name</title>
        <meta name="description" content="150–160 character description" />
        <link rel="canonical" href="https://company.com/contact" />
        <script
          type="application/ld+json"
          dangerouslySetInnerHTML={{ __html: JSON.stringify(schema) }}
        />
      </Helmet>
      {/* page content */}
    </>
  );
}
```

For shared JSON-LD (e.g. `Organization` on every page), either repeat a small `Helmet` block in a layout wrapper component rendered inside `<Routes>`, or centralize in a dedicated `<SEO />` component used by each page.

### 19.8 Rules for Cursor Code Output
- **Never** use inline `style={{}}` for design values — always use Tailwind, CSS Modules, or CSS variables
- **Never** repeat the same class string in multiple places — extract to a component or constant
- **Never** build a page as one giant component — always split into section components
- **Never** import or use **Next.js** APIs or file conventions (`next/image`, `next/link`, `next/font`, `next/head`, `next/navigation`, App Router `layout.tsx` / `page.tsx` metadata exports, Server Actions, etc.) — this project is **Vite + React**
- **Always** add `// Design token: see src/index.css` (or the repo’s actual global CSS path) comments when wiring CSS variables into Tailwind arbitrary values or shared theme extensions
- **Always** export reusable components from a central `index.ts` barrel file when the repo already uses that pattern
- **Always** use `cn()` utility (clsx + tailwind-merge) for conditional classes when Tailwind is in use
- **Always** define TypeScript interfaces (or explicit prop types) for every component; prefer explicit props over `defaultProps` on function components (React 18+ direction)
- **Always** run `vite build` before treating performance work as done; check chunk sizes and Lighthouse on `vite preview` for realistic static hosting behavior

