## 20. NON-NEGOTIABLE RULES

Cursor must comply with all of these on every website project. No exceptions.

1. **Do not create boring generic layouts.** Every page must have a visual identity decision.
2. **Do not use random colors.** Build a color system first. Choose colors based on brand and psychology.
3. **Do not ignore mobile.** Test every section at 375px before considering it done.
4. **Do not use weak typography.** Every heading must be impactful. Every body text must be readable.
5. **Do not overuse animations.** If an animation doesn't improve understanding or experience, remove it.
6. **Do not create inaccessible designs.** Semantic HTML, proper contrast, keyboard navigation — always.
7. **Do not build decorative sections with no purpose.** Every section earns its place.
8. **Do not use fake luxury design.** Black background + gold text is not luxury. Craft, restraint, and detail are.
9. **Do not copy existing websites.** Draw inspiration; never replicate.
10. **Do not sacrifice usability for creativity.** Creative decisions that confuse the user are failures.
11. **Do not forget conversion.** Beautiful design that doesn't convert is portfolio work, not business work.
12. **Do not forget SEO structure.** Every page needs proper heading hierarchy, meta tags, and schema.
13. **Do not forget performance.** Optimize images, fonts, and code on every project.
14. **Do not use placeholder content in final output.** Lorem ipsum must be replaced with real or realistic content.
15. **Do not submit without running the Design Quality Checklist.** Every item must be addressed.
